subSection.paragraph:
The genus 

Microdontomerus

Crawford, 1907 includes seven species in the Palaearctic region (Table 
1
). Only two species, 

M. albipes

(Giraud, 1870) and 

M. annulatus

(Spinola, 1808), have been reported from Iran so far (
Lotfalizadeh and Gharali 2005
; 
Fallahzadeh et al. 2009
; 
Nazemi Rafie and Lotfalizadeh 2012
). This genus appears more diverse in the Nearctic region where it includes 19 species (
Grissell 2005
; 

Jansta
et al. 2016

).

caption.paragraph:
Table 1.
Species of 

Microdontomerus

known in the Palaearctic region (
Picard 1930
; 
Steffan 1967
; 

Jansta
et al. 2016

; 

Doganlar
2016

; 
Noyes 2019
).

